uer, M., Van Der Linden, P.J., Dai, X., Maskell, K., Johnson, C.A., (2001) Climate Change 2001: The Scientific Basis, , IPCC TAR (Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change, Third Assessment Report 2001) Cambrige University Press, New York; Kristjánsson, J.E., Staple, A., Kristiansen, J., A new look at possible connection between solar activity, clouds and climate (2002) Geophys. Res. Lett., 29, pp. 2107-2110; Kuhn, J.R., Libbrecht, K.G., Nonfacular solar luminosity variation (1991) Astrophys. J. Lett., 381, pp. L35-L37; Larkin, A., Haigh, J.D., Djavidnia, S., The effect of solar UV irradiance variations on the Earth's atmosphere (2000) Space Sci. Rev., 94, pp. 199-214; Laut, P., Solar activity and terrestrial climate: An analysis of some purported correlations (2003) J. Atmos. Solar-Terr. Phys., 65, pp. 801-812; Lean, J., Short-term direct indices of solar variability (2000) Adv. Space Res., 94, pp. 39-51; Lean, J., Beer, J., Bradley, R., Reconstruction of solar irradiance since 1610: Implications for climate change (1995) Geophys. Res. Lett., 22, pp. 3195-3198; Lean, J., Rottman, G.J., Kyle, H.L., Woods, T.N., Hickey, J.R., Puga, L.C., Detection and parameterization of variations in solar-mid-and-near- ultraviolet radiation (200-400 nm) (1997) J. Geophys. Res., 102, pp. 29939-29956; Lean, J., Cook, J., Marquette, W., Johannesson, A., Magnetic sources of the solar irradiance cycle (1998) Astrophys. J., 492, pp. 390-401; Lean, J., Wang, Y.-M., Sheeley Jr., N.R., The effect of increasing solar activity on the sun's total and open magnetic flux multiple cycles: Implications for solar forcing of climate (2002) Geophys. Res. Lett., 29, pp. 2224-2227; Iii, B.L.R., Gibson, M.A., Wilson, R.S., Thomas, S., Long-term total solar irradiance variability during sunspot cycle 22 (1995) J. Geophys. Res., 100, pp. 1667-1675; Marsh, N.D., Svensmark, H., Low cloud properties influenced by cosmic rays (2000) Phys. Rev. Lett, 85, pp. 5004-5007; Mendoza, B., Estimations of Maunder minim